  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(37) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "A widow of about fourscore and four years.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The better MSS. read, “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "up to the point ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "of fourscore and four years,” pointing to the fact that this was the duration of her widowhood. Assuming her to have been married at fifteen, this places her actual age at 106. She had lived through the whole century that preceded the birth of Christ, from the death of John Hyrcanus, and had witnessed, therefore, the conquest of Judæa by Pompeius, and the rise of the Herodian house.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Which departed not from the temple.—Probably some chamber within the precincts was assigned to her, as a reputed prophetess, as seems to have been the case with Huldah (2Chronicles 34:22). Her form, bent and worn, we may believe, with age and fastings, had become familiar to all worshippers at the Temple. She, too, was one of the devout circle who cherished expectations of the coming of the Christ.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Which departed not from the temple.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Probably some chamber within the precincts was assigned to her, as a reputed prophetess, as seems to have been the case with Huldah (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Chronicles 34:22",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "). Her form, bent and worn, we may believe, with age and fastings, had become familiar to all worshippers at the Temple. She, too, was one of the devout circle who cherished expectations of the coming of the Christ.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
