        "class": "ital",
        "text": "prayers",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Rather, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "supplications",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (a more special word).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "night and day",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] ‘Night’ is put first by the ordinary Hebrew idiom (as in the Greek word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "νυχθήμερον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") which arose from their notion that ‘God made the world in six days and seven nights.’ Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 26:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “unto which promise our twelve tribes, instantly serving God night and day (Greek), hope to come.” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Timothy 5:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “she that is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "a widow indeed, and desolate",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", trusteth in God, and continueth in supplications and prayers night and day.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 2:37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ἐτῶν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "of years",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") These were the years of her whole life, not of her widowhood only. It was persons advanced in age who were the first after the angels in doing honour to the birth of the Christ: so that it might hereby be made evident that the salvation brought in by Him relates to the better life.[29]—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὁγδοήκοντα τεσσάρων",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "eighty-four",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") Therefore Anna had been about twenty-four years old when ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Jerusalem",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " had come under the power of the Romans, led by Pompey as their general.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "νηστεἰαις",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "fastings",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") even in her old age.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "[29] Which succeeds this life. For old people could have derived no good from the salvation, if it affected merely the life which they were so soon about to leave.—ED.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
